# Allowlist for GitLab -> GitHub copy.
# Same format as .gitignore; only paths matching a pattern below are copied.
#
# This is an opt-in mirror list for the OSS-safe repo contents. GitLab-only CI
# (for example .gitlab-ci.yml, pipelines/, .components.yaml) and internal/local
# metadata that should stay private (for example .env) are intentionally
# omitted and not listed here.

# GitHub and repo metadata
.gitignore
.allowed-licenses.txt
.dockerignore
.golangci.yml
.license-baseline.txt
.oss-allowlist
Makefile
README.md
go.mod
go.sum

# Source, packaging, docs, examples, and tests
api-tests/**
cmd/**
deploy/**
docker/**
examples/**
pkg/**
reval/**
scripts/**
test/**
vendor/**

# Bazel scaffold. Mirrored to GitHub so OSS users can `bazel build //...`
# and `bazel test //...` against the same sources we build internally.
# Some references inside MODULE.bazel (the distroless base image, the
# bazel-ci CI runner image) still resolve to internal NVIDIA registries;
# OSS contributors can swap MODULE.bazel's oci.pull entry for a public
# distroless base. BUILD.bazel and *.bzl under cmd/, pkg/, vendor/, etc.
# are already covered by the **-style allowlist rules above; the entries
# below cover the top-level files that no glob otherwise matches.
BUILD.bazel
MODULE.bazel
MODULE.bazel.lock
.bazelrc
.bazelversion
.bazelignore
patches/**
platforms/**
rules/**
scripts/.bazel-remote-probe
third_party/**
tools/workspace_status.sh
